  "texts": [
    "This method identifies 3,173 researchers linked to 19,381 publications and 3,127 inventions. foot_12",
    "Our final step in matching publications with inventions relies on textual similarity.",
    "We use BERT to generate textual embeddings for both paper and invention titles.",
    "We calculate the cosine similarity between their title embeddings for each potential publication-invention pair (sharing a common author and within the [-1, 3] year window).",
    "Our analysis indicates that matches with similarity scores above 0.5 likely represent publications that have contributed to an invention. foot_13"
  ],
